Q_M:\wedge^2(M)\rightarrow\wedge^4(M)
Q_M(\alpha)=\frac{1}{2}(\alpha\wedge\alpha)
Q_M(x\wedge y + u\wedge v) = x\wedge y\wedge u\wedge v
x,y,u,v \in M
Q_M(\sum_{i<j}a_{ij}e_i\wedge e_j) = q(\{a_{ij}\})e_1\wedge e_2\wedge e_3\wedge e_4
q(\{a_{ij}\})=a_{12}a_{34} - a_{13}a_{24} + a_{14}a_{23}
\alpha\in\wedge^2(M), Q_M(\alpha)=0
\alpha = u\wedge v
u, v \in M
\alpha = u\wedge v
Q_M(\alpha)=0
